title: US airlines cancel flights after aviation agency directive to cut air traffic
summary: United, Southwest, and Delta airlines will be cutting back on flights due to the ongoing government shutdown. This decision comes as they face decreased passenger demand and operational challenges. The airline industry is adapting to the uncertainties created by the shutdown's impact on travel.
